
[1]accelerate

   ACCEL'ERATE, v.t. [L. accelero, of ad and celero, to hasten, from
   celer, quick.

   1. To cause to move faster; to hasten; to quicken motion; to add to the
   velocity of a moving body. It implies previous motion or progression.

   2. To add to natural or ordinary progression; as to accelerate the
   growth of a plant, or the progress of knowledge.

   3. To bring nearer in time; to shorten the time between the present
   time and a future event; as to accelerate the ruin of a government; to
   accelerate a battle.
